# Copy to .env.local for Vite dev, or set these in your host (Vercel, Render Static, etc.).
# For local ≈ live parity, see `.env.local.example` (same keys; point VITE_API_URL at prod API if desired).
# Never commit real secrets.
#
# Production builds require VITE_API_URL with https:// (vite.config.js enforces).
# This repo includes `frontend/.env.production` (siteclonerpro.com) so `npm run build` matches Render.
# Local dev: optional. If unset, the app calls same-origin /api and Vite proxies to VITE_DEV_API_PROXY.
# For the bundled backend+SPA launch path in this repo, local production-style runs commonly use http://127.0.0.1:3050.
# VITE_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:3050
# VITE_DEV_API_PROXY=http://127.0.0.1:3050

# Must match backend CLONEAI_INGRESS_KEY when that env is set (sent as X-CloneAI-Key).
# Repo-root Docker on Render: set CLONEAI_INGRESS_KEY on cloneai-api only — the image build reuses it for Vite (no separate VITE_CLONEAI_KEY unless you override).
# VITE_CLONEAI_KEY=

# If the API is served on the same origin as this app (reverse proxy), you can use:
# VITE_SAME_ORIGIN_API=true
# and omit VITE_API_URL in some setups (see main.js).
#
# Repo-owned browser verification uses the same built app path; keep this aligned with the public app/API origin.

# Optional: meta name="cloneai-api-origin" in index.html or window.__CLONEAI_API_BASE__ before load.

# VITE_PUBLIC_APP_URL=https://siteclonerpro.com
# VITE_TURNSTILE_SITE_KEY=
#
# Subscriptions and one-time runs use Stripe on the API (no Stripe publishable key required in this SPA).
